	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. mil. 72. He may have been a quaestor under Pompey when he died at Aenus in 67 (Plut. Cat. Min. 11; Badian, Studies 42), to the great sorrow of his half-brother Cato. See MRR 2.119, 121, note 3. ,\n" .
